// to check if a string is palindrome or not
bool isPalindrome(string s) {
    int n = s.length();
    for (int i = 0; i < n / 2; i++) {
        if (s[i] != s[n - i - 1]) {
            return false;
        }
    }
    return true;
}

    s.substr(i)
📌Returns the substring of s starting at index i to the end.

Example: If s = "abcde" and i = 2, then s.substr(2) → "cde"

📌 s.substr(0, i)
Returns the first i characters of s.

Example: If s = "abcde" and i = 2, then s.substr(0, 2) → "ab"

📌 Combined: s.substr(i) + s.substr(0, i)
Concatenates the two parts: from i to end, then beginning to i.

This is equivalent to rotating the string s left by i characters.





